'''State of the Onion''' is a book written by [[Julie Hyzy]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=HTbt2xdMNywC&source=gbs_navlinks_s|title=State of the Onion|last=Hyzy|first=Julie|date=2008-01-02|publisher=Penguin|isbn=9781101206522|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.juliehyzy.com/chef.html|title=White House Chef mystery series|website=www.juliehyzy.com|access-date=2017-03-25}}</ref> and published by [[Berkley Books]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/978-0-425-21869-3|title=Fiction Book Review: State of the Onion by Julie Hyzy, Author . Berkley $7.99 (325p) ISBN 978-0-425-21869-3|work=PublishersWeekly.com|access-date=2017-03-25|language=en}}</ref> (owned by [[Penguin Group]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=http://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/300165/state-of-the-onion-by-julie-hyzy/|title=State of the Onion by Julie Hyzy {{!}} PenguinRandomHouse.com|language=en-US}}</ref>) on 2 January 2008, which later went on to win the [[Anthony Award]] for Best Paperback Original in 2009.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bouchercon.com/anthony-awards/winners-and-nominees/2000s/|title=Winners and Nominees 2000s|date=2015-09-22|work=Bouchercon|access-date=2017-03-25|language=en}}</ref>
